quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  93,1,By the morning day light
  93,2,and by the night when it covers with darkness
  93,3,"your Lord has neither forsaken you, O Muhammad, nor is He displeased"
  93,4,Certainly the later period shall be better for you than the earlier
  93,5,Soon your Lord shall grant you something with which you will be well-pleased
  93,6,Did He not find you an orphan and give you shelter
  93,7,Did He not find you lost and gave you guidance
  93,8,Did He not find you poor and made you self-sufficient
  93,9,"Therefore, do not treat the orphan with harshness"
  93,10,and do not chide away the beggar
  93,11,and rehearse the bounty of your Lord